---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Garden Studios & Home Offices Frankston | No-Permit Builds | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Garden studios, home offices and teen retreats in Frankston and the Peninsula. Below 25m² / 3.6m height = no planning permit needed in most zones. $25K-$95K depending on plumbing."
  canonical="https://frankstongrannyflats.com.au/services/garden-studios/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">No permit, fast turn-around</span>
      <h1>Garden studios &amp; home offices in <span class="accent">Frankston &amp; the Peninsula</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        12&ndash;25m&sup2;, single room, can include a bathroom. Below the 25m&sup2; / 3.6m
        height threshold = no planning permit needed in most residential zones. Home
        office, teen retreat, hobby workshop, art studio, podcast room.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free consultation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>The no-permit advantage (mostly).</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <p>
          The Victoria Building Regulations exempt single-storey outbuildings <strong>under
          25m&sup2; floor area, 3.6m maximum height, and not used for habitable
          purposes</strong> from needing a planning permit in most residential zones.
          That means a properly-sized garden studio can go from contract to keys in
          <strong>6&ndash;10 weeks</strong> with no council delay &mdash; faster than
          almost any other build category.
        </p>
        <p>
          Catches: it must be a genuine non-habitable space (no permanent sleeping,
          no full kitchen), the 25m&sup2; rule excludes Mornington Peninsula Shire&rsquo;s
          Design and Development Overlays in some cases, and any plumbing or
          drainage still needs a building permit (not the same as a planning permit).
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">What we build in this category.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Home office 12&ndash;18m&sup2; (no plumbing):</strong> Wired for high-speed data, separate-meter electrical option, double-glazed for thermal performance, acoustic ceiling for video calls. <strong>$25K&ndash;$45K</strong> all-in.</li>
          <li><strong>Studio with bathroom 18&ndash;25m&sup2;:</strong> Adds toilet + basin + shower (plumbed via main house sewer). Crosses into building-permit territory. <strong>$50K&ndash;$85K</strong>.</li>
          <li><strong>Teen retreat 15&ndash;25m&sup2;:</strong> Single bed alcove, study desk, small wet bar (sink + bar fridge only, no full kitchen), sound isolation. <strong>$40K&ndash;$70K</strong>.</li>
          <li><strong>Hobby workshop / garage studio:</strong> Higher ceiling option (still under 3.6m), reinforced floor for equipment, three-phase power if needed. <strong>$30K&ndash;$60K</strong>.</li>
          <li><strong>Art / podcast studio:</strong> North-light glazing for artists, acoustic treatment + isolation for podcast/music. <strong>$45K&ndash;$95K</strong>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">When a garden studio is NOT the right answer.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>You want it as accommodation for an ageing parent &mdash; need a 1-bedroom granny flat instead</li>
          <li>You want to rent it out &mdash; need a 1-bedroom granny flat with planning permit</li>
          <li>You&rsquo;re in an overlay (HO heritage, DDO design controls, BMO bushfire) &mdash; check before relying on the no-permit pathway</li>
          <li>Block is &lt;400m&sup2; &mdash; outdoor area requirements still apply even for non-habitable structures</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Common Peninsula garden studio specs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Slab: 100mm reinforced (or steel-bearer for sloped sites)</li>
          <li>Frame: pine 90mm or steel cee-section for clear-span</li>
          <li>Cladding: Hardies Linea, Colorbond, or natural timber to suit garden setting</li>
          <li>Roof: Colorbond or membrane flat-pitch for height-restricted sites</li>
          <li>Insulation: R2.5 walls, R5.0 ceiling (above the non-habitable minimum &mdash; comfort matters)</li>
          <li>Electrical: 8-12 outlets, dedicated 20A circuit, optional data conduit</li>
          <li>Climate: split-system reverse-cycle (most common) or just ceiling fan + insulation for milder use</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Where we work.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/frankston-south/">Frankston South</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mt-eliza/">Mt Eliza</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington/">Mornington</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/carrum-downs/">Carrum Downs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/seaford/">Seaford</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington-peninsula/">Full Peninsula</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free garden studio consultation.</h2>
        <p>No-permit pathway check, build in 6-10 weeks. Free site visit.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
